media.headline: Travis' RBI single
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Travis drives in the first run of the game
media.bigblurb: Devon Travis rips a line drive into right, scoring Justin Smoak and giving the Blue Jays a 1-0 lead in the top of the 3rd inning

media.headline: Jones' two-run shot
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Jones hammers a two-run shot to left
media.bigblurb: Adam Jones crushes a two-run home run to left for his first of the season, giving the Orioles a 2-1 lead in the bottom of the 3rd inning

media.headline: Pillar's spectacular grab
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Pillar denies Machado of extra bases
media.bigblurb: Kevin Pillar reaches up and scales the center-field wall to rob Manny Machado of extra bases in the bottom of the 3rd inning

media.headline: O'Day catches Davis' solo homer
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Davis crushes solo shot, O'Day catches it
media.bigblurb: Chris Davis crushes his 200th homer with the Orioles over the center-field wall where it is caught by Darren O'Day in the Orioles' bullpen

media.headline: Brach's clutch strikeout
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Brach fans Donaldson to escape jam
media.bigblurb: Brad Brach strikes out Josh Donaldson to end the 8th inning, stranding a runner on third to keep the Orioles up, 3-1

media.headline: Happ K's Davis
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Happ strikes out Davis looking
media.bigblurb: J.A. Happ strikes out Chris Davis looking in the bottom of the 2nd inning for his first K of the 2017 season

media.headline: Bundy K's Travis
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Bundy strikes out Travis swinging
media.bigblurb: Dylan Bundy strikes out Devon Travis swinging in the top of the 1st inning for his first K of the 2017 season

media.headline: Britton earns the save
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Britton induces double play for the save
media.bigblurb: Zach Britton gets Steve Pearce to ground into a game-ending double play, converting his 50th consecutive save in the Orioles' 3-1 victory

media.headline: Machado's creative cleats
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Machado's cleats have many cool features
media.bigblurb: Manny Machado's cleats include Skittles embedded inside and engraved initials of himself, his wife and his dog

media.headline: Bundy strikes out eight
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Bundy fans eight over seven innings
media.bigblurb: Dylan Bundy strikes out eight Blue Jays over seven innings of work, allowing just one run on four hits to earn the win

media.headline: Statcast: Pillar robs Machado
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Statcast analyzes Pillar robbing Machado
media.bigblurb: Blue Jays outfielder Kevin Pillar makes a catch at the wall on a liner with an 86% hit probability, robbing extra bases from Manny Machado

media.headline: Davis on 200th O's homer
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Davis hammers oppo-field shot in victory
media.bigblurb: Orioles first baseman Chris Davis discusses his 200th home run with the O's and his power to all parts of the park

media.headline: Happ strikes out nine
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Happ fans nine over seven innings
media.bigblurb: J.A. Happ strikes out nine Orioles over seven innings of work, allowing three runs on five hits

media.headline: Showalter on win over Blue Jays
media.blurb: TOR@BAL: Showalter on Bundy's dominating effort
media.bigblurb: O's manager Buck Showalter talks about the quick pace of the game, Toronto's challenging pitching staff and Dylan Bundy's start

media.headline: Recap: TOR 1, BAL 3
media.bigblurb: Daily Recap: Adam Jones and Chris Davis both went deep, while Dylan Bundy stuck out eight over seven frames to earn the win

media.headline: Gibbons on 3-1 loss to Orioles
media.bigblurb: Blue Jays manager John Gibbons talks about his team's hitting struggles in its 3-1 loss to the Orioles
